The listeners of the curdel learned the Portuguese language, and then reading [7]. From the end of the 19th century. famous engravings began to appear on the covers of brochures. Collections of literature de Courdelle are still published with similar images on the covers [8]. and can be 8, 16, 32, or 64 pages[9]. With the advent of personal computers, printers, and photocopiers, many kurdels can be self-printed on offset paper using 1/4 A4 size booklets called "xerokurdels"[10] .